The Herald Presumptive tax legislation was introduced to broaden the revenue base in view of the increase in informal business activities. Selected sectors of the economy were targeted to ensure the participation of informal businesses in tax payment. Self-employed professionals presumptive tax With effect from January 1, 2021 there was a new insertion on the sectors that pay presumptive tax. This insertion added professionals to the lists of categories subject to presumptive tax. The presumptive tax is paid by self-employed professionals who would not have submitted income tax returns for the previous year of assessment. Self-employed professional is an individual who earns income, on his or her own account or as a member of a partnership, as: 